Package: dls
Version: 1.0
Date: 2018-01-01
Title: dynamic light scattering data processing
Author: Tamás Haraszti [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Tamás Haraszti <haraszti@dwi.rwth-aachen.de>
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Suggests:
Description: Dynamic light scattering or photon-correlation spectroscopy measures the fluctuations of the light intensity in a small volume of a suspension and establishes particle sizes based on the autocorrelation and its relation to the translational diffusion process. The core is a Stokes-Einstein relation. This package is a colleciton of tools to summarize the autocorrelation function and its analysis towards particle size distributions.
